---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Raga Bhairav — Deep Study | Harmonium Halt"
  description="The majestic dawn raga — serious, devotional, profound. Complete study with composition. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Raga Bhairav — Deep Study</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-advanced capitalize">advanced</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 50 min · Advanced</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Raga Bhairav — Deep Study</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">The majestic dawn raga — serious, devotional, profound. Complete study with composition.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Morning raga performed at dawn (4 to 7 AM)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Uses komal Re and komal Dha — the defining features</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Vadi: Ga (natural). Samvadi: Komal Dha</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Pakad: S r S comma G M d P comma d P M G r S</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Rasa: Veera (heroic) and Shanta (peaceful)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>The Majesty of Bhairav</h2>
      <p>Raga Bhairav is one of the oldest and most revered ragas in Hindustani classical music. Its name evokes Shiva — the cosmic transformer. Performed at the break of dawn Bhairav captures the serious devotional mood of early morning when the world is quiet and the mind is naturally inclined toward contemplation. Many musicians consider it the most profound raga of all.</p>

      <h2>Complete Profile</h2>
      <p>Thaat: Bhairav. Jati: Sampurna. Aroha: S r G M P d N upper-S. Avaroha: upper-S N d P M G r S. Vadi: Ga. Samvadi: Komal Dha. Time: Early morning 4 to 8 AM. Rasa: Veera and Shanta. Characteristic notes: Komal Re and Komal Dha are the two notes that uniquely identify Bhairav.</p>

      <h2>Aroha and Avaroha</h2>
      <p>Aroha keys: A W D F G Y J K. Avaroha keys: K J Y G F D W A. Practice the Komal Re (W key) and Komal Dha (Y key) with extra deliberateness — these two swaras define the raga. Notice how different Bhairav sounds from a natural major scale due to these two komal swaras. The combination creates a serious almost austere quality.</p>

      <h2>Pakad and Key Phrases</h2>
      <p>Main pakad: S r S comma G M d P comma d P M G r S. This sweeping pakad traverses the full range of Bhairav. Key phrase 1: r S r S — komal Re oscillating to Sa — unmistakably Bhairav. Key phrase 2: d P M G — komal Dha descending to Pa then to Ga. Practice each phrase independently before combining them in flowing improvisation.</p>

      <h2>Composition in Bhairav</h2>
      <p>Sthayi: S r G M bar P d P M G. Antara: d N upper-S comma r upper-G r upper-S bar N d P M G r S. Practice this composition in very slow tempo — Vilambit. Bhairav is a raga that requires and rewards slowness. Every note especially komal Re and komal Dha should be savored and held slightly longer than technically necessary. This is the emotional soul of Bhairav.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>